dialogue.text: Can you tell me when your symptoms started and if they have been getting worse over time?
My symptoms started about a month ago. They seem to get worse after I do any physical activity, but they improve quite a bit after I rest.
Have you noticed any difficulty swallowing, speaking, or changes in your facial expressions?
I haven't noticed any difficulty swallowing or speaking, and my facial expressions seem normal to me. It's mostly just the double vision and weakness in my arms.
Have you experienced any drooping of your eyelids, especially as the day goes on or after using your eyes for a while?
I haven't noticed any drooping of my eyelids, but I do feel more strain on my eyes as the day goes on, especially when I'm working.
Have you had any recent infections, fevers, or illnesses before these symptoms began?
I haven't had any recent infections, fevers, or illnesses before these symptoms started. I felt completely fine until about a month ago when everything began.
Have you noticed any muscle weakness in your legs or difficulty walking, or is it mainly in your upper limbs?
I've mainly noticed the weakness in my upper limbs, especially when trying to brush my hair or lift things. My legs feel okay, but I do have some difficulty climbing stairs.
Have you noticed any changes in your breathing, such as shortness of breath or difficulty taking deep breaths, especially after exertion?
I haven't experienced any shortness of breath or difficulty taking deep breaths. My breathing feels normal, even after exertion.
Have you noticed any muscle twitching, cramping, or unusual sensations like numbness or tingling in your arms or elsewhere?
I haven't noticed any muscle twitching or cramping, and I don't have any numbness or tingling in my arms or anywhere else. It's mostly just the weakness and double vision that I'm dealing with.
Have you ever experienced similar symptoms in the past, or is this the first time you've had these issues with weakness and double vision?
This is the first time I've experienced these issues with weakness and double vision. I've never had anything like this before.
Have you noticed if your symptoms are worse at certain times of the day, such as in the evening or after prolonged activity?
I've noticed that my symptoms tend to worsen as the day goes on, especially after I've been working for a while. It feels like the more I use my eyes or my arms, the more fatigued they become.
Have you noticed any improvement in your symptoms after taking naps or resting for a short period during the day?
Yes, I do notice a significant improvement in my symptoms after I take a nap or rest for a short period. It feels like my strength and vision get better after I give myself some time to recover.
Have you noticed any changes in your voice, such as it becoming softer or more nasal, especially after talking for a while?
I haven't noticed any changes in my voice. It sounds normal to me, even after talking for a while. My main concerns are still the double vision and weakness in my arms.
Have you noticed any rashes, joint pain, or other symptoms elsewhere in your body, such as dry mouth or dry eyes?
I haven't noticed any rashes or joint pain, and my mouth and eyes feel normal. It's really just the double vision and weakness that I'm focused on.
Have you ever been diagnosed with any autoimmune diseases or thyroid problems in the past?
I haven't been diagnosed with any autoimmune diseases or thyroid problems in the past. My health has been pretty stable until these recent symptoms started.
Have you noticed any recent weight loss, changes in appetite, or night sweats since your symptoms began?
I haven't noticed any recent weight loss or changes in my appetite, and I haven't experienced any night sweats either. My eating habits have remained the same throughout this time.
Have you noticed any drooping of your head or difficulty holding your head up as the day progresses?
I haven't noticed any drooping of my head or difficulty holding it up. I feel like my neck strength is okay, but I do get tired overall as the day goes on.
Have you ever experienced any episodes where your vision completely blacked out or you lost consciousness, even briefly?
I haven't experienced any episodes where my vision completely blacked out or lost consciousness. My vision has just been double, but I haven't had any complete loss of sight or fainting.
Have you noticed any improvement in your symptoms after taking cold showers or being in a cool environment, or do they worsen with heat?
I haven't really tried cold showers, but I do feel like my symptoms can worsen with heat. When it's warm, I notice the double vision and weakness seem to get a bit worse.
Have you noticed any changes in your pupils, such as them becoming unusually large or small, or any difficulty focusing on objects up close?
I haven't noticed any changes in my pupils; they seem normal to me. I also don't have any difficulty focusing on objects up close, but the double vision makes it hard to see clearly at times.
Have you ever tried any over-the-counter medications or supplements to help with your symptoms, and if so, did you notice any improvement or worsening after taking them?
I haven't tried any over-the-counter medications or supplements for my symptoms yet. I wanted to discuss it with you first before trying anything.
Thank you for sharing that. Have you noticed any recent changes in your mood, memory, or ability to concentrate since your symptoms began?

I haven't noticed any significant changes in my mood or memory, but I do find it a bit harder to concentrate when my symptoms are worse. It's frustrating trying to focus on my work with the double vision and weakness.

Can you tell me when you first noticed the problems with your walking and coordination? Have these symptoms been getting worse over time?
I first noticed the problems with my walking about a month ago. It has definitely been getting worse; my friends say I look like I'm stumbling around.
Have you experienced any other symptoms, such as dizziness, double vision, slurred speech, or weakness in your arms or legs?
I haven't had any dizziness or double vision, but I do feel some weakness in my right arm. My legs also feel unsteady when I try to walk.
Have you had any recent infections, fevers, or illnesses before these symptoms started? Also, do you have any history of alcohol use or exposure to toxins?
I haven't had any recent infections or fevers, and I don't have a history of alcohol use or exposure to toxins. My focus has mostly been on managing my other health issues.
Can you tell me more about your other health issues? Do you have any chronic conditions or past neurological problems?

I have Crohn disease, which I've been dealing with for the past two years. It's been quite severe and hasn't responded well to standard treatments. Other than that, I haven't had any neurological problems in the past.
Thank you for sharing that. Are you currently taking any medications for your Crohn disease, such as steroids, immunosuppressants, or biologics? If so, which ones?
I'm currently on natalizumab for my Crohn disease, which I've been taking for the past year. I haven't been on any other medications like steroids or immunosuppressants recently.
Thank you for clarifying your medication history. Have you noticed any changes in your mental status, such as confusion, memory problems, or personality changes?
I haven't noticed any confusion or memory problems, but I do feel a bit more frustrated with my situation lately. My mood has been affected by the challenges I'm facing with my walking.
Have you experienced any changes in your vision, such as blurred vision or loss of vision in one or both eyes?
I haven't experienced any changes in my vision, like blurred vision or loss of vision. My eyesight seems to be fine.
Have you had any trouble with swallowing, speaking clearly, or controlling your facial muscles? Any numbness or tingling in your face or limbs?
I haven't had any trouble with swallowing or speaking clearly, and my facial muscles seem to be fine. I do feel some weakness in my right arm, but no numbness or tingling in my face or limbs.
Have you noticed any involuntary movements, tremors, or muscle stiffness? Also, have you had any recent falls or injuries related to your unsteady gait?
I haven't noticed any involuntary movements or tremors, but I do feel some stiffness in my right arm. I haven't fallen yet, but I worry that I might if this keeps getting worse.
Thank you for sharing that. Have you had any recent changes in your bowel or bladder control, such as incontinence or urgency?
I haven't had any changes in my bowel or bladder control. Everything seems to be normal in that regard.
Have you ever had any previous MRI scans of your brain or spinal cord? If so, do you know if there were any abnormalities found?
I haven't had any previous MRI scans of my brain or spinal cord, so I'm not sure if there were any abnormalities. This is the first time I'm experiencing these kinds of symptoms.
Thank you for letting me know. Have you noticed any changes in sensation, such as numbness, tingling, or loss of feeling in your arms, legs, or elsewhere on your body?
I haven't noticed any numbness or tingling in my arms or legs, and I still have normal sensation everywhere else. It's mostly just the weakness and unsteadiness that I'm concerned about.
Have you experienced any headaches, nausea, or vomiting recently? Also, have you noticed any hearing loss or ringing in your ears?
I haven't experienced any headaches, nausea, or vomiting lately. My hearing seems normal, and I haven't noticed any ringing in my ears either.
Have you noticed any changes in your coordination or ability to perform tasks with your hands, such as buttoning a shirt or writing? Are you having trouble with fine motor skills?
I have noticed some difficulty with fine motor skills, especially when trying to button my shirt or write. My right hand feels weaker, and it's frustrating to manage everyday tasks.
Thank you for sharing that. Have you noticed any muscle wasting or changes in the appearance of your right hand or arm, such as thinning or twitching of the muscles?
I haven't noticed any muscle wasting or significant changes in the appearance of my right hand or arm. It just feels weaker and a bit stiff at times.
Have you experienced any recent weight loss, night sweats, or fevers? Also, have you traveled recently or been exposed to anyone with infectious diseases?
I haven't experienced any recent weight loss, night sweats, or fevers. I haven't traveled recently either, and I haven't been around anyone with infectious diseases.
Have you noticed any changes in your speech, such as slurring or difficulty finding words, even if mild? Also, do you have any family history of neurological diseases?
I haven't noticed any slurring or difficulty finding words; my speech seems normal. As for family history, there are no known neurological diseases in my family.
Have you noticed any changes in your mood, behavior, or personality beyond feeling frustrated? For example, increased irritability, apathy, or depression?

I haven't noticed any significant changes in my mood or behavior beyond feeling frustrated. I do feel a bit more down about my situation, but I wouldn't say I'm experiencing depression or irritability.
Have you had any recent vaccinations, blood transfusions, or surgeries in the past year? Also, have you ever been tested for HIV or other immunodeficiency conditions?
I haven't had any recent vaccinations, blood transfusions, or surgeries in the past year. I haven't been tested for HIV or any other immunodeficiency conditions either.
Thank you for clarifying. Given your history of natalizumab use and new neurological symptoms, I’d like to check for any abnormalities in your brain. REQUEST TEST: Brain_MRI with contrast

RESULTS: MRI Brain findings show lesions consistent with Progressive Multifocal Encephalopathy (PML). T1/T2 images reveal multifocal demyelinating lesions without gadolinium enhancement, indicative of PML.

Can you tell me when the feeding difficulties and abdominal distension first started? Have there been any changes in the frequency or consistency of his stools?
The feeding difficulties started a few days ago, and he seems to cry a lot when I try to feed him. His stools have been normal, but I haven't noticed any changes in frequency or consistency.
Has he had any episodes of vomiting, and if so, what does the vomit look like? Has he had any fevers or signs of illness such as cough or runny nose?
No, he hasn't had any episodes of vomiting, and I haven't noticed any fevers or signs of illness like a cough or runny nose. He just seems really uncomfortable and fussy.
Has he had any problems with passing urine, or have you noticed any swelling in his legs or around his eyes?
No, he hasn't had any problems with passing urine, and I haven't noticed any swelling in his legs or around his eyes. He seems to be urinating normally.
Has he had any recent weight loss or failure to gain weight as expected? Have you noticed any visible veins on his abdomen or any changes in the color of his skin?

He hasn't had any weight loss; in fact, I believe he has been gaining weight despite the feeding issues. I haven't noticed any visible veins on his abdomen or any changes in the color of his skin either.
Have you noticed if his abdomen feels firm or tender when you touch it, or if it seems larger after feeding? Has he had any trouble breathing or rapid breathing?
His abdomen feels firm and seems to be distended, especially after feeding. He hasn't had any trouble breathing or rapid breathing, but he does cry a lot when I touch his belly.
Thank you for sharing that. Has he had any history of constipation or difficulty passing stools in the past, even if his stools are currently normal? Have you noticed any blood in his stool or mucus?
He hasn't had any history of constipation or difficulty passing stools before, and I haven't noticed any blood or mucus in his stool. Everything seems normal in that regard.
Has he had any recent infections, such as a cold or diarrhea, in the past few weeks? Also, was he born full-term, and were there any complications during pregnancy or delivery?
No, he hasn't had any recent infections like a cold or diarrhea. He was born full-term at 39 weeks, and there were no complications during pregnancy or delivery.

Have you noticed any lumps or masses in his abdomen when you touch it, or any changes in his appetite besides the feeding difficulties? Has he had any episodes of excessive sweating, especially during feeds?
I haven't noticed any lumps or masses in his abdomen, but his appetite has definitely decreased. He hasn't had any episodes of excessive sweating during feeds either.
Has there been any family history of metabolic or genetic disorders, or any similar symptoms in siblings or close relatives? Also, has he received all his routine vaccinations up to this point?
There’s no family history of metabolic or genetic disorders, and he doesn’t have any siblings. He has received all his routine vaccinations so far.
Thank you. Has he had any recent changes in his activity level, such as being more lethargic or less interactive than usual? Have you noticed any unusual movements or episodes of staring spells?
He seems to be a bit more fussy and less interactive than usual, especially when I try to play with him. I haven't noticed any unusual movements or staring spells, though.
Has he had any recent illnesses or hospitalizations in the past? Also, have you noticed any signs of jaundice, such as yellowing of the eyes or skin?
No, he hasn't had any recent illnesses or hospitalizations. I haven't noticed any signs of jaundice, and his eyes and skin look normal to me.
Thank you. When you touch his abdomen, does it feel like there is fluid inside (a wave-like movement), or is it just firm and swollen? Also, have you noticed any changes in his urine color or output?
When I touch his abdomen, it feels firm and swollen, but I don't notice any wave-like movement. His urine color seems normal, and he appears to be urinating regularly.
Thank you. Has he had any recent trauma or injury to his abdomen? Also, have you noticed any signs of pain when he moves his legs or hips?
No, he hasn't had any recent trauma or injury to his abdomen. He does seem to cry when I move his legs or hips, which makes me think he might be in pain.
Thank you for sharing that. Have you noticed any swelling or masses in his groin area, or any changes in the appearance of his scrotum?
I haven't noticed any swelling or masses in his groin area, and his scrotum looks normal to me.
Thank you. Has he had any recent changes in the color or consistency of his stools, such as pale or clay-colored stools, or any episodes of diarrhea?
No, his stools have been normal in color and consistency, and I haven't seen any episodes of diarrhea. Everything seems fine in that regard.
Thank you. Has he had any recent changes in his breathing pattern, such as grunting, nasal flaring, or chest retractions, especially when he is feeding or crying?
No, I haven't noticed any changes in his breathing pattern like grunting, nasal flaring, or chest retractions. He breathes normally, even when he's crying or feeding.

Thank you. Has he had any recent exposure to sick contacts, or has anyone in the household been ill recently? Also, have you noticed any signs of developmental delay, such as not meeting expected milestones for his age?
No, he hasn't had any recent exposure to sick contacts, and no one in the household has been ill. As for developmental milestones, he seems to be meeting them, but he is a bit fussier than usual.
Thank you. On physical examination, is there any palpable mass in the abdomen, or do you notice any asymmetry or bulging in a particular area?
I don't feel any palpable mass in his abdomen, but there does seem to be some bulging in the lower part of his belly. It feels quite firm to the touch.
Thank you for that information. Has the bulging in the lower abdomen changed in size over the past few days, or does it seem to get worse after feeding or when he cries?
The bulging in his lower abdomen seems to get worse after feeding and when he cries. It hasn't changed much in size over the past few days, but it definitely feels firmer during those times.
Thank you. To help clarify the cause of the abdominal distension and bulging, I’d like to request an imaging study. REQUEST TEST: Abdominal_Ultrasound
RESULTS: NORMAL READINGS

How long have you been experiencing these symptoms, and did they start gradually or suddenly?
I've been experiencing these symptoms for about 4 weeks now. They started gradually, but the neck swelling just appeared in the last 4 days.
Have you noticed any fevers, chills, or recent infections? Also, have you had any recent travel or exposure to sick contacts?
I haven't had any fevers or chills, and I haven't traveled recently. I also haven't been around anyone who was sick.
Have you noticed any changes in your appetite or any difficulty swallowing or breathing due to the neck swelling?
I've noticed a decrease in my appetite, and I do feel some discomfort when swallowing, but breathing hasn't been an issue.
Have you experienced any other symptoms such as cough, shortness of breath, or chest pain?
I haven't experienced any cough or shortness of breath, and I don't have any chest pain. Just the fatigue and abdominal pain are really bothering me.
Have you noticed any bruising, unusual bleeding, or persistent infections recently? Also, have you had any night sweats that soak your sheets?
I haven't noticed any bruising or unusual bleeding, but I have been having night sweats that soak my sheets almost every night. It's been quite uncomfortable.
Have you noticed any other lumps or swollen areas elsewhere on your body, such as under your arms or in your groin? Also, have you had any recent unintentional weight loss, and if so, how much?
I haven't noticed any lumps or swollen areas under my arms or in my groin. I have lost about 5.4 kg (12 lb) recently without trying.
Have you had any previous history of cancer, autoimmune diseases, or chronic illnesses? Also, do you have any family history of similar symptoms or serious illnesses?
I don't have any previous history of cancer or autoimmune diseases, and my past medical history is pretty clear. As for family history, there aren't any serious illnesses that I know of.
Have you experienced any recent infections, dental issues, or skin wounds that could have led to lymph node swelling? Also, do you smoke or use alcohol or any other substances?
I haven't had any recent infections, dental issues, or skin wounds that I can think of. I do smoke about a pack a day and drink alcohol socially.
Have you noticed any drenching sweats during the day, persistent itching, or rashes anywhere on your body? Also, have you had any recent unexplained fevers, even if mild?
I haven't had any drenching sweats during the day, and I don't have any rashes or persistent itching. No unexplained fevers either, just the night sweats that are quite bothersome.
Have you noticed any pain or tenderness in the enlarged lymph node, or is it painless? Also, have you experienced any nausea, vomiting, or changes in your bowel habits?
The enlarged lymph node is painless, which is a bit concerning. I haven't experienced any nausea or vomiting, but my bowel habits have been normal.
Have you noticed any jaundice (yellowing of your skin or eyes), or any swelling in your legs or abdomen? Also, have you had any recent unintentional injuries or trauma to your abdomen?
I haven't noticed any jaundice or yellowing of my skin or eyes. There is some unusual fullness in my belly area, but I haven't had any recent injuries or trauma to my abdomen.

Have you noticed any early satiety (feeling full quickly when eating) or any palpable lumps or masses in your abdomen? Also, have you had any recent changes in your energy levels or ability to perform daily activities?
I've been feeling unusually full in my belly area, and it's been difficult to eat my usual portions. My energy levels have definitely decreased, making it hard to keep up with my daily activities.

Have you noticed any drenching sweats at night that require you to change your clothes or sheets? Also, have you experienced any recent infections, such as a sore throat or dental issues, before the lymph node swelling appeared?

Yes, I've been having night sweats that soak my sheets almost every night, which is really uncomfortable. I haven't had any recent infections, sore throat, or dental issues before the lymph node swelling started.
Have you noticed any other symptoms such as back pain, bone pain, or frequent headaches? Also, have you had any recent unexplained fevers, even if mild?
I haven't experienced any back pain, bone pain, or frequent headaches. No unexplained fevers either, just the persistent night sweats and fatigue.
Have you noticed any changes in your skin color, such as pallor or easy bruising? Also, have you had any recent unexplained cough, hoarseness, or difficulty speaking?
I haven't noticed any changes in my skin color, and I don't have easy bruising. I also haven't had any cough, hoarseness, or difficulty speaking.

Have you experienced any recent or past unexplained weight gain or swelling in your face, hands, or feet? Also, have you noticed any persistent abdominal pain in a specific area, or is it more generalized?
I haven't experienced any unexplained weight gain or swelling in my face, hands, or feet. The abdominal pain is more generalized, but it has been worsening over the past few weeks.
Have you noticed any feverish sensations at night, or chills accompanying your night sweats? Also, have you had any recent blood tests or imaging studies done for these symptoms?
I haven't noticed any feverish sensations or chills with my night sweats. I haven't had any recent blood tests or imaging studies done for these symptoms either.
Thank you for clarifying. Have you noticed any difficulty with urination, blood in your urine or stool, or any recent changes in your menstrual cycle (if applicable)?
I haven't noticed any difficulty with urination or blood in my urine or stool. I'm not experiencing any menstrual cycle changes, as I'm male.
Have you experienced any recent loss of appetite for specific foods, or any new food aversions? Also, have you noticed any persistent cough, even if it's mild or dry?
I have noticed a loss of appetite overall, but I haven't had any specific food aversions. I also haven't experienced any persistent cough, mild or dry.
Thank you for your response. On physical exam, is the enlarged supraclavicular lymph node hard or rubbery, fixed or mobile, and approximately what size is it?
The enlarged supraclavicular lymph node feels rubbery and is mobile. It's about the size of a grape.

Can you tell me how long you have been experiencing fatigue, flank pain, and fever? Did these symptoms start before, during, or after your antibiotic treatment for sinusitis?
I've been experiencing fatigue, flank pain, and fever for about two weeks now. These symptoms started after I finished my antibiotic treatment for sinusitis.
Did you notice any changes in your urination, such as pain, increased frequency, urgency, or blood in your urine?
I haven't noticed any changes in my urination, such as pain, increased frequency, urgency, or blood in my urine. Everything seems normal in that regard.
Have you experienced any nausea, vomiting, or loss of appetite along with your other symptoms?
I haven't experienced any nausea or vomiting, but I do feel a bit less hungry than usual. My appetite isn't what it normally is.
Have you noticed any swelling in your legs, ankles, or around your eyes? Additionally, have you had any recent weight changes?
I haven't noticed any swelling in my legs, ankles, or around my eyes. As for weight changes, I haven't really kept track, but I feel like I've lost a little weight recently.
Have you had any chills or night sweats along with your fever? Also, have you traveled recently or had any recent hospitalizations or procedures?
I haven't had any chills or night sweats, but the fever has been persistent. I haven't traveled recently, and I haven't had any hospitalizations or procedures either.
Have you noticed any rashes, joint pain, or new headaches since your symptoms began? Also, do you have any history of kidney problems or autoimmune diseases?
I did have a rash during my antibiotic treatment, but that has resolved now. I haven't experienced any joint pain or new headaches. I don't have a history of kidney problems or autoimmune diseases.
Thank you for sharing that. Can you tell me which antibiotic you were prescribed for your sinusitis, and if you have any known drug allergies?
I was initially prescribed amoxicillin for my sinusitis, and after developing a rash, it was changed to cephalexin. I don't have any known drug allergies.
Thank you for clarifying. Since your symptoms started after antibiotic use and you had a rash, have you noticed any dark-colored urine or yellowing of your skin or eyes?
I haven't noticed any dark-colored urine or yellowing of my skin or eyes. Everything seems normal in that regard.
Have you experienced any difficulty breathing, chest pain, or palpitations since your symptoms began?
I haven't experienced any difficulty breathing, chest pain, or palpitations. My breathing feels normal, and my heart seems to be beating regularly.
Have you noticed any swelling or tenderness in your neck, armpits, or groin, or any lumps anywhere on your body?
I haven't noticed any swelling or tenderness in my neck, armpits, or groin, and I haven't felt any lumps anywhere on my body. Everything seems normal in that regard.
Have you noticed any new back pain or pain that radiates to your groin? Also, have you had any recent sore throat or upper respiratory symptoms aside from your sinusitis?
I haven't noticed any new back pain or pain radiating to my groin. Aside from my sinusitis, I haven't had any recent sore throat or upper respiratory symptoms.
Have you noticed any foamy urine or changes in the amount of urine you produce? Also, do you have a history of high blood pressure or diabetes?
I haven't noticed any foamy urine or changes in the amount of urine I produce; everything seems normal there. I do have a history of high blood pressure, but no diabetes.
Thank you for sharing that. Have you recently taken any over-the-counter medications, herbal supplements, or NSAIDs (like ibuprofen or naproxen) in addition to your prescribed antibiotics?
I haven't taken any over-the-counter medications, herbal supplements, or NSAIDs recently. I've mostly just been sticking to my prescribed medications.
Have you noticed any bruising, bleeding gums, or unusual bleeding anywhere else since your symptoms began?
I haven't noticed any bruising, bleeding gums, or unusual bleeding anywhere else. Everything seems normal in that regard.
Have you experienced any shortness of breath when lying flat or upon exertion, or any episodes of confusion or difficulty concentrating since your symptoms began?
I haven't experienced any shortness of breath when lying flat or upon exertion, and I haven't had any episodes of confusion or difficulty concentrating. My mental clarity seems to be fine.
Have you noticed any muscle aches or joint stiffness, or have you had any recent insect bites or exposure to animals?
I haven't noticed any muscle aches or joint stiffness. I also haven't had any recent insect bites or exposure to animals.
Have you noticed any swelling or tenderness in your abdomen, particularly around the area where you feel the flank pain? If I press gently on your flanks, does it make the pain worse?
I haven't noticed any swelling or tenderness in my abdomen. When you press gently on my flanks, it does make the pain a bit worse.
Thank you for letting me know. Have you experienced any recent episodes of sore throat, or noticed blood in your urine at any point, even if it was just once?
I haven't had any recent episodes of sore throat, and I haven't noticed any blood in my urine at any point. Everything seems normal in that regard.
Thank you for clarifying. Have you ever had similar symptoms in the past, or is this the first time you’ve experienced this combination of fatigue, flank pain, and fever?
This is the first time I've experienced this combination of fatigue, flank pain, and fever. I've had other health issues in the past, but nothing quite like this.
Thank you for sharing that. To help narrow things down, have you noticed any swelling or tenderness in your joints, or any mouth sores since your symptoms began?
I haven't noticed any swelling or tenderness in my joints, and I haven't had any mouth sores either. Everything seems normal in that regard.

Can you describe exactly where on your knee the pain is located? Is it on the front, back, inside, or outside of the knee?
The pain is located on the inside of my knee, just below the kneecap. It feels sharp and has been getting worse since it started.
Did the pain start suddenly during a specific activity, or did it come on gradually over time? Also, does anything make the pain better or worse, such as rest or movement?
The pain started suddenly while I was playing volleyball, especially when I was pivoting and twisting. It gets worse with movement, but resting seems to help a little.
Have you noticed any swelling, bruising, or instability in your knee since the pain began? Are you able to bear weight on that leg without difficulty?
I haven't noticed any swelling or bruising, and my knee feels stable. I can bear weight on it, but it does hurt when I put pressure on that leg.
Have you heard or felt any popping or snapping sensation in your knee at the time of injury or since then? Also, do you have any locking or catching when you try to move your knee?
I didn't hear or feel any popping or snapping at the time of the injury. There hasn't been any locking or catching when I move my knee either.
Have you experienced any numbness, tingling, or weakness in your leg or foot since the pain started? Also, does the pain radiate anywhere, or is it localized just below the kneecap on the inside?
I haven't experienced any numbness, tingling, or weakness in my leg or foot. The pain is localized just below the kneecap on the inside and doesn't radiate anywhere else.

Have you had any previous injuries to this knee, or any history of knee problems in the past? Also, have you tried any treatments like ice, compression, or over-the-counter pain medications, and did they help?

I haven't had any previous injuries to this knee or any history of knee problems. I haven't tried any treatments yet, but I was thinking about using ice and maybe taking some over-the-counter pain medication to see if that helps.
Have you noticed any difficulty fully straightening or bending your knee since the pain started? Also, does the pain worsen when going up or down stairs?
I haven't noticed any difficulty fully straightening or bending my knee, but the pain does get worse when going up or down stairs. It feels particularly sharp during those movements.
Have you noticed any tenderness if you press on the area just below the kneecap on the inside of your knee? Also, does the pain worsen when you try to squat or kneel?
Yes, it is tender when I press on that area just below the kneecap on the inside. The pain does worsen when I try to squat or kneel; it feels quite uncomfortable.
Thank you for clarifying. Have you noticed any creaking or grinding sensations (crepitus) in your knee when you move it, or does it feel smooth when bending and straightening?
I haven't noticed any creaking or grinding sensations in my knee; it feels relatively smooth when I bend and straighten it.

Thank you for your response. Have you recently changed your exercise routine, increased the intensity or frequency of your physical activity, or started any new sports or activities before the pain began?
Yes, I recently joined a volleyball team and have been participating in practices that involve a lot of pivoting and twisting movements. I think that might have contributed to the pain.

Thank you for sharing that. When you press on the tender area just below the kneecap on the inside, does it feel like the pain is right over the bone, or does it seem to be more in the soft tissue or tendon?
It feels more like the pain is in the soft tissue or tendon rather than right over the bone. The tenderness is quite pronounced in that area.
Thank you for clarifying. Have you noticed any morning stiffness in your knee, or does the pain seem to improve after you’ve been moving around for a while?
I haven't noticed any morning stiffness in my knee. The pain tends to improve a bit after I've been moving around, but it still hurts during certain activities.
Thank you for your response. When you jump or land from a jump, does the pain become significantly worse? Also, have you noticed any changes in the appearance of the area, such as redness or warmth?
I haven't tried jumping or landing from a jump yet, but I can imagine it would hurt more. I haven't noticed any redness or warmth in the area either; it looks normal to me.

Thank you for your response. When you press on the tender area, does it feel like a very specific spot is painful (like you can point to it with one finger), or is the pain more spread out over a larger area?
The pain feels like a very specific spot that I can point to with one finger. It's quite localized just below the kneecap on the inside of my knee.
